(365, 0, '2016-11-03 05:10:56', '2016-11-03 05:10:56', '<p>Step1: Go to below path</p>\n<blockquote><p>C:\\xampp\\apache\\conf\\extra</p>\n<p>open file : httpd-vhosts.conf</p>\n<p>Add :</p>\n<p>&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt; </p>\n<p>ServerName localhots.com </p>\n<p>DocumentRoot acess_path(C:/xampp/htdocs/..) </p>\n<p>&lt;Directory acess_path(C:/xampp/htdocs/..)&gt; </p>\n<p>Options FollowSymLinks </p>\n<p>AllowOverride All </p>\n<p>Order allow,deny </p>\n<p>Allow from all </p>\n<p>&lt;/Directory&gt;</p>\n<p>&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Step2: </p>\n<blockquote><p>Go to below path :</p>\n<p>C:\\Windows\\System32\\drivers\\etc</p>\n<p>open this file hosts: </p>\n<p>(prefer opne in notepad ++ to editable)</p>\n<p>Entry your host name :</p>\n<p>127.0.0.1   localhots.com</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Step3 :</p>\n<blockquote><p>Restart xampp or wamp</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thanks &#x1f642;  </p>\n', 'How to create Vhost in window for xampp?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-create-vhost-in-window-for-xampp', '', '', '2016-11-03 05:29:19', '2016-11-03 05:29:19', '', 0, 'http://programmerlab.com/dwqa-question/how-to-create-vhost-in-window-for-xampp/', 0, 'dwqa-question', '', 1),
(366, 1, '2016-11-03 05:27:19', '2016-11-03 05:27:19', 'Step1 :\r\n<blockquote>\r\nYou need to have XAMPP installed ( &#x1f610; )\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep2 :\r\n<blockquote>\r\nOpen up the Xampp control panel and stop Apache (Ensure that you dont have it running as a service  this is where doing so complicates things)\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep3:\r\n<blockquote>\r\nNavigate to C:/xampp/apache/conf/extra or wherever you installed xampp\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep4 :\r\n<blockquote>\r\nFire up your text editor with administrative privileges and\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep5:\r\n<blockquote>\r\nOpen up httpd-vhosts.conf found in the C:/xampp/apache/conf/extra folder\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep6: At the very bottom of the file paste the following\r\n<blockquote>\r\n&lt;VirtualHost *:80&gt;\r\nDocumentRoot "C:/xampp/htdocs/laravel/public"\r\nServerName localhost.dev\r\nServerAlias www.localhost.dev\r\n&lt;Directory "c:/xampp/htdocs/laravel/public"&gt;\r\nAllowOverride All\r\nRequire all Granted\r\n&lt;/Directory&gt;\r\n&lt;/VirtualHost&gt;\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep6: Go to following path\r\n<blockquote>\r\nC:/Windows/System32/drivers/etc/hosts, where hosts is the file.\r\nopen this file and add following code.\r\n127.0.0.1       localhost.dev\r\n</blockquote>\r\n\r\nStep7 :\r\n<blockquote>\r\nRestart Apache and test to make sure it is working\r\n</blockquote>\r\n', 'Answer for How to create Vhost in window for xampp?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'answer-for-how-to-create-vhost-in-window-for-xampp', '', '', '2016-11-03 05:27:19', '2016-11-03 05:27:19', '', 365, 'http://programmerlab.com/dwqa-answer/answer-for-how-to-create-vhost-in-window-for-xampp/', 0, 'dwqa-answer', '', 0),
(371, 0, '2016-11-15 15:36:59', '2016-11-15 15:36:59', '<strong>Solution :</strong>\r\nStep1 :Create .htaccess file in root folder of your laravel application\r\nStep2: Add following code in .htaccess file\r\n<blockquote>&lt;IfModule mod_rewrite.c&gt;\r\n&lt;IfModule mod_negotiation.c&gt;\r\nOptions -MultiViews\r\n&lt;/IfModule&gt;\r\nRewriteEngine On\r\n# Redirect Trailing Slashes...\r\nRewriteRule ^(.*)/$ /$1 [L,R=301]\r\n# Handle Front Controller...\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d\r\nRewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f\r\nRewriteRule ^ index.php [L]\r\n&lt;/IfModule&gt;</blockquote>\r\nStep3: copy index.php from public folder and paste it on root\r\nStep4: Find and Replace following code from index.php\r\n<blockquote>require __DIR__.''/../bootstrap/autoload.php'';\r\nto\r\nrequire __DIR__.''/bootstrap/autoload.php'';\r\nAnd</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>$app = require_once __DIR__.''/../bootstrap/app.php'';</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>to</blockquote>\r\n<blockquote>$app = require_once __DIR__.''/bootstrap/app.php'';</blockquote>\r\nStep5: open following file\r\n<blockquote>sudo gedit /etc/apache2/sites-available/000-default.conf\r\nand\r\nAdd following code\r\n\r\n&lt;Directory /var/www/html&gt;\r\nOptions Indexes FollowSymLinks MultiViews\r\nAllowOverride All\r\nOrder allow,deny\r\nallow from all\r\n&lt;/Directory&gt;</blockquote>\r\nStep5: Save and restart apache\r\n<blockquote>sudo service apache2 restart</blockquote>\r\nThanks :) it wllwork for you !', 'Remove index.php from URL in laravel framework ?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'remove-index-php-from-url-in-laravel-framework', '', '', '2016-11-15 15:48:28', '2016-11-15 15:48:28', '', 0, 'http://programmerlab.com/dwqa-question/remove-index-php-from-url-in-laravel-framework/', 0, 'dwqa-question', '', 0),
(373, 0, '2016-11-17 08:01:33', '2016-11-17 08:01:33', '<strong>Solution :</strong>\r\nStep1: Remove previos installed php version using following command.\r\n<blockquote>\r\nsudo apt-get purge `dpkg -l | grep php| awk ''{print $2}'' |tr "\\n" " "`\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep2: Add the PPA\r\n<blockquote>\r\nsudo add-apt-repository ppa:ondrej/php\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep3: Install your PHP Version\r\n<blockquote>\r\nsudo apt-get update\r\nsudo apt-get install php5.6\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep4: Install php5.6 modules\r\n<blockquote>\r\nsudo apt-get install php5.6-mbstring php5.6-mcrypt php5.6-mysql php5.6-xml\r\n</blockquote>\r\nStep5: Verify your version\r\n<blockquote>\r\nsudo php -v\r\n</blockquote>', 'How to Install PHP5.6 in ubuntu?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'how-to-install-php5-6-in-ubuntu', '', '', '2016-11-17 08:01:33', '2016-11-17 08:01:33', '', 0, 'http://programmerlab.com/dwqa-question/how-to-install-php5-6-in-ubuntu/', 0, 'dwqa-question', '', 0),
