(396, 1, '2016-12-29 12:41:25', '2016-12-29 12:41:25', '<blockquote><strong>What is Doctrine?</strong>\r\n\r\nDoctrine 2 is an object-relational mapper (ORM) for PHP 5.4+ that provides transparent persistence for PHP objects. It uses the Data Mapper pattern at the heart, aiming for a complete separation of your domain/business logic from the persistence in a relational database management system.\r\n\r\nThe benefit of Doctrine for the programmer is the ability to focus on the object-oriented business logic and worry about persistence only as a secondary problem. This doesnt mean persistence is downplayed by Doctrine 2, however it is our belief that there are considerable benefits for object-oriented programming if persistence and entities are kept separated\r\n\r\n&nbsp;</blockquote>', 'Doctrine', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'doctrine', '', '', '2017-03-25 19:32:28', '2017-03-25 19:32:28', '', 0, 'http://programmerlab.com/?page_id=396', 0, 'page', '', 0),
