(399, 1, '2016-12-29 12:45:30', '2016-12-29 12:45:30', '<blockquote><strong>What is Doctrine?</strong>\r\n\r\nDoctrine 2 is an object-relational mapper (ORM) for PHP 5.4+ that provides transparent persistence for PHP objects. It uses the Data Mapper pattern at the heart, aiming for a complete separation of your domain/business logic from the persistence in a relational database management system.\r\n\r\nThe benefit of Doctrine for the programmer is the ability to focus on the object-oriented business logic and worry about persistence only as a secondary problem. This doesnt mean persistence is downplayed by Doctrine 2, however it is our belief that there are considerable benefits for object-oriented programming if persistence and entities are kept separated</blockquote>', 'Doctrine', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '396-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-12-29 12:45:30', '2016-12-29 12:45:30', '', 396, 'http://programmerlab.com/2016/12/29/396-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
