(415, 1, '2017-01-10 09:51:10', '2017-01-10 09:51:10', 'Step 1. Run this command php\n<blockquote>artisan doctrine:convert:mapping from-database annotation app/Entities</blockquote>\nThis command will read database schema and create the entities with annotation mapping in my ./app/Entities location\n\nStep 2.\n<blockquote>php artisan doctrine:generate:entities generate-annotations= "true" app/Entities</blockquote>\nThis will create entity classes with getter and setter methods from your mapping information.\n\nThis command will create entity classes with getter and setter methods from your mapping information.  app/Entities\\ in the path from your\n\n"app/Entity" : This is your entity file path.', 'how-to-generate-doctrine-entities-for-existing-schema-in-laravel', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '412-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-01-10 09:51:10', '2017-01-10 09:51:10', '', 412, 'http://programmerlab.com/2017/01/10/412-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
